"title": "4315: clay",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4315",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Clay was a basic building material in biblical times and clay pottery was widely used.</p>\n<h2>Clay pottery</h2>\n<h3>Moulded by potters</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer18:3-Jer18:4\">JER 18:3–18:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:16\">ISA 29:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:25\">ISA 41:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:9\">ISA 45:9</a></p>\n<h3>Used to make pots</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:28\">LEV 6:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:33\">LEV 11:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:5\">LEV 14:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:50\">LEV 14:50</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:12\">LEV 15:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam4:2\">LAM 4:2</a></p>\n<h3>Used to make jars</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer19:1-Jer19:3\">JER 19:1–19:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num5:17\">NUM 5:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:14\">JER 32:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:7\">2CO 4:7</a></p>\n<h2>Other uses of clay</h2>\n<h3>To make idols</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:31-Dan2:35\">DAN 2:31–2:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:41-Dan2:45\">DAN 2:41–2:45</a></p>\n<h3>To make moulds</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:46\">1KI 7:46</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr4:17\">2CH 4:17</a></p>\n<h3>To make bricks</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah3:14\">NAM 3:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer43:9\">JER 43:9</a></p>\n<h3>In plastering</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:42\">LEV 14:42</a></strong></p>\n<h3>To make furnaces</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps12:6\">PSA 12:6</a></strong></p>\n<h3>To seal documents</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:14\">JOB 38:14</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Clay tablets were used for writing on</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek4:1\">EZK 4:1</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Clay was a relatively weak material</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job13:12\">JOB 13:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job4:18-Job4:19\">JOB 4:18–4:19</a></p>\n<h2>Clay was a very common material</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job27:16\">JOB 27:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:20\">2TI 2:20</a></p>\n<h2>God and his people compared to a potter and the clay</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa64:8\">ISA 64:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job10:9\">JOB 10:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job33:6\">JOB 33:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer18:6\">JER 18:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:19-Rom9:21\">ROM 9:19–9:21</a></p>",
